events.description: The release of Angola's annual and monthly inflation data for January 2026.

facts.fact_text: Angola's annual inflation rate fell to 14.56% in January 2026 from 15.70% in December.

evidences.evidence_text: Angola’s annual inflation rate eased further to 14.56% in January 2026 from 15.70% in December

facts.fact_text: The January 2026 inflation rate is the lowest since August 2023.

evidences.evidence_text: marking the softest increase since August 2023

facts.fact_text: Monthly CPI increased by 0.68% in January 2026.

evidences.evidence_text: On a monthly basis, the CPI rose by 0.68% in January, following a 0.95% increase in the previous month.

facts.fact_text: Food and non-alcoholic beverages inflation slowed to 14.89% in January 2026.

evidences.evidence_text: led by food and non-alcoholic beverages (14.89% vs 16.15% in December 2025)

claims.claim_text: The stability of the kwanza was a key driver in the reduction of inflation.

evidences.evidence_text: The stability of the kwanza has been a crucial factor.

evidence.evidence_text: The stability of the kwanza has been a crucial factor.
Inflation slowdowns were seen across most categories, led by food and non-alcoholic beverages
